        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 19. 1877</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Will you be so good as to correct the following unfortunate misprint which produces a mistake of some importance:</p> 
<figure type="diagram"> 
<p>Cross &amp; Self-Fertilisation</p>
<p>p 275. line 6 from top</p>
<p>For ‘self-fertilised’ read ‘crossed’<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p> </figure> 
<p>My dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Carus was translating <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8595.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Cross and self fertilisation</hi></ref> into German (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10807.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 20 January 1877</ref>). For CD’s corrections to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9316.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Cross and self fertilisation</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10877.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. V. Carus, 4 March 1877</ref> and n. 2.</note>
        </div>        
            
